- The 'time difference' refers to the difference in days between when a test was conducted (`test_date`) and when the coverage data was recorded (`coverage_date`); 
- 'more than a day' implies that the query looks for instances where this average difference is more than 1 day; 
- 'considering different coverage types' means the query groups results by `coverage_type`, indicating an interest in how this relationship varies across different types of coverage (e.g., Functional, Random, Directed).
